SUBSECTION.TEXT:

        When we introduced the substitution model in
        section we showed how the combination
        (f 5)f(5) evaluates to 136, given the following
        procedurefunction
        definitions:


          f_example

            (define (square x)
            (* x x))

            (define (sum-of-squares x y)
            (+ (square x) (square y)))

            (define (f a)
            (sum-of-squares (+ a 1) (* a 2)))


function square(x) {
    return x * x;
}

function sum_of_squares(x, y) {
    return square(x) + square(y);
}

function f(a) {
    return sum_of_squares(a + 1, a * 2);
}
